  - M7/M8 chroma coeff-rate CB double-count. C `skip_chroma_rate_est`
    (full_loop.c:1922, coeff_rate_est_lvl 2) writes the CB approximation
    (3000+cb_eob*500) directly into the *cb_coeff_bits accumulator when
    cb_eob < th, then `return false` at the CR check when cr_eob >= th WITHOUT
    clearing it; the caller (svt_aom_full_loop_uv, full_loop.c:2660) then adds
    the full estimate: *cb_coeff_bits += cb_txb_coeff_bits. So CB is priced
    approx + full ONLY in the cb_eob<th && cr_eob>=th case (CB checked first).
    The funnel priced CB clean -> undercharged H-mode candidates ~4500 ->
    flipped leaf y_mode. -> preset 7 36/60 -> 57/60 (first divergence op ~8850
    for SB(224,192) now IDENTICAL); preset 8 + 10 unchanged (no regression).
